#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an10.34"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.34:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.34:0.2"
msgid "4. Upālivagga "
msgstr "4. With Upāli "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.34:0.3"
msgid "34. Upasampadāsutta "
msgstr "34. Ordination "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an10.34:1.1"
msgid "“Katihi nu kho, bhante, dhammehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabban”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, how many qualities should a mendicant have to give ordination?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.34:1.2"
msgid "“Dasahi kho, upāli, dhammehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ. "
msgstr "“Upāli, a mendicant should have ten qualities to give ordination. "

msgctxt "an10.34:1.3"
msgid "Katamehi dasahi? "
msgstr "What ten? "

msgctxt "an10.34:1.4"
msgid "Idhupāli, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, conducting themselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken. "

msgctxt "an10.34:1.5"
msgid "bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā; "
msgstr "They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically. "

msgctxt "an10.34:1.6"
msgid "pātimokkhaṃ kho panassa vitthārena svāgataṃ hoti suvibhattaṃ suppavattaṃ suvinicchitaṃ suttaso anubyañjanaso; "
msgstr "Both monastic codes have been passed down to them in detail, well analyzed, well mastered, well judged in both the rules and accompanying material. "

msgctxt "an10.34:1.7"
msgid "paṭibalo hoti gilānaṃ upaṭṭhātuṃ vā upaṭṭhāpetuṃ vā; "
msgstr "They’re able to care for the sick or get someone else to do so. "

msgctxt "an10.34:1.8"
msgid "paṭibalo hoti anabhiratiṃ vūpakāsetuṃ vā vūpakāsāpetuṃ vā; "
msgstr "They’re able to settle dissatisfaction or get someone else to do so. "

msgctxt "an10.34:1.9"
msgid "paṭibalo hoti uppannaṃ kukkuccaṃ dhammato vinodetuṃ; "
msgstr "They’re able to dispel remorse when it has come up. "

msgctxt "an10.34:1.10"
msgid "paṭibalo hoti uppannaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ dhammato vivecetuṃ; "
msgstr "They’re able to rationally dissuade someone from misconceptions that come up. "

msgctxt "an10.34:1.11"
msgid "paṭibalo hoti adhisīle samādapetuṃ; "
msgstr "They’re able to encourage someone in the higher ethics, "

msgctxt "an10.34:1.12"
msgid "paṭibalo hoti adhicitte samādapetuṃ; "
msgstr "the higher mind, "

msgctxt "an10.34:1.13"
msgid "paṭibalo hoti adhipaññāya samādapetuṃ. "
msgstr "and the higher wisdom. "

msgctxt "an10.34:1.14"
msgid "Imehi kho, upāli, dasahi dhammehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabban”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant should have these ten qualities to give ordination.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.34:1.15"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

